ZH: 别随便给人贴标签，我们都是独特的个体。
EN: Don't label people so easily, we are all unique individuals.

ZH: 他们总是喜欢把我贴上懒惰的标签。
EN: They always like to label me as lazy.

ZH: 我们不能仅仅因为外表就贴标签。
EN: We can't just label people based on appearances.

ZH: 每个人都有自己的故事，不要轻易贴标签。
EN: Everyone has their own story, don't label them easily.

ZH: 不要被社会的标签束缚，做自己想做的事。
EN: Don't be constrained by society's labels, do what you want to do.

ZH: 他们总是把我们这一代年轻人贴上懒惰的标签。
EN: They always label our generation as lazy.

ZH: 很多人对他们身上的负面标签感到沮丧。
EN: Many people feel discouraged by the negative labels on them.

ZH: 别为了满足自己的标签，而迷失了自己的本质。
EN: Don't lose yourself trying to conform to labels.

ZH: 我们无法确定别人是什么人，所以不要轻易贴标签。
EN: We can't determine who others are, so don't label them easily.

ZH: 不要被别人的看法所束缚，贴上你不想要的标签。
EN: Don't be constrained by others' views, by labeling you with labels you don't want.

ZH: 我很讨厌社会上关于性别的标签。
EN: I really hate the gender labels in society.

ZH: 他把我们所有人都贴上了不负责任的标签。
EN: He has labeled all of us as irresponsible.

ZH: 在教育领域中，对学生贴标签是不恰当的。
EN: It is inappropriate to label students in the field of education.

ZH: 我们的行为不能完全由别人给我们贴上标签。
EN: Our behavior should not be solely labeled by others.

ZH: 这个社会总是喜欢给人贴上各种不同的标签。
EN: This society always likes to label people with different labels.

ZH: 不应该因为一个人的性取向而给他们贴上标签。
EN: One should not be labeled based on their sexual orientation.

ZH: 他们对不同社会阶层的人都有不同的标签。
EN: They have different labels for people of different social classes.

ZH: 贴标签只会让人变得局限，不如了解实际情况。
EN: Labeling only limits people, it's better to understand the actual situation.

ZH: 他们没有给这个项目贴上成功的标签。
EN: They did not label this project as a success.

ZH: 我们应该看到每个人的潜力，而不是给他们贴上失败的标签。
EN: We should see the potential in everyone, rather than labeling them as failures.
